/* CSS Coding Guidelines
------------------------------------

- Group styles using @group for happy editing in 
	CSSEdit, and (i think) others. (see example below.)

- Alphabetize attributes

- Comment, comment, comment.

- Use shorthand whenever possible.
	padding: 1em 2em 3em 4em;
	The order is: top, right, bottom, left
	
	A nice guide: http://www.dustindiaz.com/css-shorthand/
	
- Declare colors in the site controller.
	Use the form:
	:light_green => '#363636'
	
	The first bit is a name for the color.
	Next comes the color itself, quoted.
	
	You can refer to colors in the stylesheet using ruby
	using the following format:
	<%
	#       <%= @colors[:light_green] %>
	%>
	
- When adding images for use in the interface, 
	describe them in the "Images" section below.
	
	If aplicable, note the original source of the image.

*/

